    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_AlterDomainAndChangeColumnDomain",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to alter the domain (user-defined data type) of columns in tables and views within a SQL Server database. It takes two parameters: the old domain name and the new domain name. The procedure is intended to update columns that use a specific user-defined data type to a new data type and refresh views that depend on these columns. However, the procedure is currently commented out, meaning it does not execute any operations."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level of this stored procedure is medium. It involves dynamic SQL execution, cursor operations, and conditional logic to handle both tables and views. The procedure also interacts with a user-defined view ("
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Utils.uvw_FindAllTablesColumnsByUserDefinedDatatype",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ") to retrieve metadata about tables and columns, adding to its complexity."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
